<br>
If people are telling you to use wurmslayer mainhand, it could be for 2 reasons.<br>
<br>
a) -- Primary only<br>
b) -- You are under level 45. (which I don't know, so I'm asking)<br>
<br>
The &quot;fastest weapon mainhand&quot; logic is based upon your mainhand having a damage bonus.  This comes largely at level 50+.  If you don't have a huge damage bonus for your mainhand, like from levels 1-45ish or so, then the fastest weapon logic does not apply, and best ratio applies instead. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ushadowtiger.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shadowtiger</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/4/02 8:18:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1628.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: RE: off hand hits...</span><hr size=1> Scim of the Emerald dawn is a pretty sick ratio: 20/34 is mothing to sneeze at.  That's the same (in your off hand) as a 10/17 waepon.<br>
